content:
Add Items to the Channel Menu

Select and edit your preferred customer channels to appear in your website menu.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Channel Menu setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Performance, Professional, Unlimited, and Essentials


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Channel Menu:	Customize Application AND Modify Metadata

From Channel Menu Settings, select Edit for Menu Setup to start adding your items.
Type your Menu Item Name, select or type the Channel Type, and search for your Deployment. The default icon for each channel appears on the setup window.
Click the Add Item button after each channel. Add up to six channels for your website.
Change the order of the menu items with the up and down arrow buttons. The channels appear in the menu in the order of the left column.
Use the Delete Menu Item button to remove channels.

To hide a channel for specific user operating systems, check the appropriate boxes in Advanced Settings.
Click Save when all your channels have been added.
TIP Use the + symbol with a country code for your number when adding the phone channel if you have international customers.
IMPORTANT Keep the Show this menu item box checked under Default Display. Uncheck the box if using the Channel Menu Reordering API.
